Key Match Events: Andrew Heaney received run support from his teammates in a 7-4 series-clinching win vs. the Los Angeles Angels.
Marcus Semien hit a solo home run and Nathaniel Lowe hit a two-run home run in the top of the first inning.
Andrew Heaney allowed three earned runs on three hits, one walk, and eight strikeouts in six innings.
Heaney earned his first win since July 21 vs. the Baltimore Orioles.
Post-Match Reflections: Andrew Heaney expressed happiness about the run support and his performance.
Marcus Semien commented on Heaney's pitching, stating that Heaney is having a career year despite his record.
